summary: In this context, 1,1,2,2-tetrachloroethene is mentioned as one of the compounds analyzed within two multivariate data sets, specifically in relation to the Scheldt estuary. The term 'analyte' refers to any substance being analyzed or measured, which includes 1,1,2,2-tetrachloroethene as part of the study's focus on environmental contaminants. However, there is no detailed discussion of the specific relationship or significance of 1,1,2,2-tetrachloroethene as an analyte beyond its inclusion in the data sets.
